-most-employees-say-no%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20respond%20to%20engagement%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20meaningful%20way%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Quantum%20Workplace%20survey%20of%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20workers.%20%26quot%3BEmployee%20surveys%20mostly%20seem%20like%20a%20way%20for%20the%20executive%20suite%20to%20pat%20themselves%20on%20the%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Gaudio%2C%20the%20creative%20director%20at%20the%20Austin-based%20chatbot%20startup%20Manychat%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20believe%20in%20the%20power%20of%20anonymity%20to%20induce%20honesty%2C%20but%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20power%20dynamic%20is%20always%20there%2C%20hanging%20over%20the%20head%20of%20their%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20experienced%20a%20surprising%20assertion%20of%20this%20power%20dynamics%20firsthand%20%E2%80%94%20my%20bosses%20didn't%20like%20my%20answers%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it%20%E2%80%94%20in%20general%2C%20the%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%20for%20this%20story%20placed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-are-avoiding-the-office-because-of-their-bosses-survey-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esurveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20taxonomic%20rank%20of%20workplace%20annoyances%20somewhere%20around%20%26quot%3Bfilling%20out%20timesheets.%26quot%3B%20Surveys%20can%20be%20annoying%20because%20they're%20persistent%2C%20doubly%20so%20when%20you%20perceive%20that%20your%20employers%20won't%20do%20much%20with%20the%20results.%20This%20can%20lead%20to%20survey%20fatigue%2C%20where%20the%20response%20rate%20falls%20off%20a%20cliff%20after%20being%20asked%20to%20submit%20too%20many.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20constantly%20filing%20your%20anonymous%20grievances%20into%20an%20anonymous%20digital%20suggestion%20box%2C%20you%20may%20begin%20to%20wonder%20not%20if%20the%20survey%20will%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuccessful-businesses-secret-funding-job-company-growth-money-financing-startups-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimprove%20your%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20if%20you%20aren't%20perhaps%20participating%20in%20a%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bsnitchware.%26quot%3B%20Are%20you%20voluntarily%20telling%20on%20yourself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20survey%20the%20history%20of%20surveys%2C%20we%20find%20that%20they%20were%20once%20considered%20novel%2C%20exciting%2C%20and%20based%20in%20real%20utility%2C%20much%20as%20the%20kanban%20project%20management%20board%20was%20born%20out%20of%20a%20working%20system%20in%20a%20real%20factory.%20Before%20World%20War%20I%2C%20most%20bosses%20were%20primarily%20concerned%20with%20their%20employees'%20external%20lives%20and%20work%20outcomes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20inner%20toils%20and%20happiness%20quotients%20mattered%20very%20little%2C%20as%20the%20historian%20Sanford%20Jacoby%20wrote%20in%20a%202008%20paper%20called%20%26quot%3BEmployee%20Attitude%20Surveys%20in%20Historical%20Perspective.%26quot%3B%20But%20strikes%20and%20wartime%20labor%20shortages%20gave%20the%20workforce%20some%20modicum%20of%20power.%20This%20gave%20the%20educational%20psychologist%20J.%20David%20Houser%20the%20perfect%20platform%20to%20take%20the%20%26quot%3Bconsumer%20attitude%20studies%26quot%3B%20he'd%20been%20doing%20on%20behalf%20of%20public%20utilities%20into%20an%20entirely%20new%20field%20of%20study%3A%20employee%20satisfaction%20and%20morale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3EBy%20the%20early%201940s%2C%20satisfaction%20surveys%20found%20a%20champion%20in%20the%20armed%20forces.%20Because%20soldier%20morale%20began%20to%20be%20considered%20paramount%20to%20defense%20success%2C%20the%20military%20took%20the%20results%20of%20personnel%20surveys%20seriously.%20This%20led%20to%20some%20drastic%20changes%2C%20including%20introducing%20combat%20badges%2C%20requiring%20psychological%20evaluations%20for%20returned%20soldiers%2C%20and%20even%20helping%20along%20the%20eventual%20desegregation%20of%20the%20armed%20forces.%20(Today%2C%20the%20government's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopm-probationary-workers-fired-elon-musk-doge-trump-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOffice%20of%20Personnel%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%20notably%20conducts%20agency-%20and%20government-wide%20surveys%20as%20a%20resource%20for%20the%20public%20trust.)%20Decades%20later%2C%20Kahn%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20godfather%20of%20employee%20engagement%2C%26quot%3B%20set%20up%20a%20brilliant%20framework%20for%20understanding%20employee%20satisfaction%20outside%20the%20binary%20of%20happy%2Fsad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20anonymity%20that%20Gaudio%20railed%20against%20can%20also%20promote%20a%20kind%20of%20equity.%20Jenna%20Eichberg%2C%20the%20chief%20people%20officer%20at%20AlertMedia%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20because%20surveys%20aggregate%20an%20entire%20organization's%20feedback%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20overindex%20your%20worry%20about%20the%20loudest%20outliers.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20chase%20one%20person.%20You're%20here%20to%20serve%20a%20majority%20of%20your%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20and%20the%20beauty%20of%20the%20big%20dataset%20is%20that%20you%20can%20hear%20just%20as%20much%20from%20shy%20employees%2C%20or%20from%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who're%20different%20than%20the%20ones%20who%20mostly%20talk%20to%20you%20in%20person.%26quot%3B%20Phil%20Wilburn%2C%20the%20VP%20of%20people%20analytics%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkday-ceo-doge-government-contracts-federal-agencies-on-prem-migration-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWorkday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20agrees.%20A%20survey%2C%20he%20tells%20me%20over%20email%2C%20%26quot%3Bgives%20people%20who%20might%20not%20feel%20comfortable%20speaking%20up%20in%20a%20meeting%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they're%20introverted%2C%20more%20junior%2C%20or%20part%20of%20an%20underrepresented%20group%20%E2%80%94%20a%20safe%20space%20to%20share%20their%20thoughts.%20And%20it%20helps%20managers%20respond%20to%20those%20concerns%20thoughtfully%2C%20without%20putting%20anyone%20on%20the%20spot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Eichberg%20says%2C%20if%20your%20employees%20don't%20feel%20heard%2C%20it's%20because%20you're%20not%20making%20them%20feel%20heard.%20%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20mistake%20organizations%20make%20is%20they%20do%20all%20these%20surveys%20and%20they%20collect%20all%20this%20data%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20actually%20do%20something%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BOr%20they%20do%20something%20with%20it%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20go%20back%20and%20tell%20their%20workforce%20what%20they%20did%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%20The%20head%20of%20people%20at%20a%20small%20LA-based%20startup%20tells%20me%20that%20his%20organization%20similarly%20seems%20to%20freeze%20whenever%20a%20surprising%20result%20or%20answer%20pops%20out%20of%20the%20survey%20black%20box.%20%26quot%3BI%20tell%20my%20CEO%20that%20by%20the%20time%20a%20comment%20winds%20up%20in%20the%20survey%2C%20it's%20already%20tried%20to%20reach%20you%20some%20other%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Surveys%2C%20he%20continues%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bonly%20as%20good%20as%20the%20relationships%20between%20the%20people%20in%20the%20company%20and%20only%20as%20effective%20as%20the%20executives%20who%20have%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20anonymity%20can%20lend%20itself%20to%20candor%20and%20equity%2C%20it%20might%20still%20sometimes%20fail%20in%20the%20way%20of%20promoting%20actual%20conversation%20and%20trust.%20Consider%20a%202021%20survey%20from%20The%20Workforce%20Institute%20that%20found%20that%20only%2037%25%20of%20entry-level%20employees%20believe%20their%20colleagues%20are%20completely%20honest%20in%20their%20answers%20and%20assessments.%20If%2043%25%20of%20workers%20fear%20retaliation%20for%20speaking%20up%20at%20work%2C%20per%20a%20survey%20from%20the%20Institute%20of%20Business%20Ethics%2C%20anonymity%20can%20only%20help%20so%20much.%20In%20the%20same%20way%20remote%20employees%20have%20learned%20to%20keep%20their%20Slack%20icon%20%26quot%3Bgreen%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20avoid%20suspicion%20of%20blowing%20off%20work%2C%20some%20workers%20have%20self-taught%20to%20never%20be%20entirely%20honest%20with%20their%20HR%20surveys.%20Last%20year%20at%20Amazon%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-commandment-office-work-shibboleth-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20Andy%20Jassy%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20a%20memo%20requiring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-layoffs-quit-jobs-hybrid-remote-work-office-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efive-days-a-week%20RTO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20touching%20on%20connection%20and%20communication%20as%20principal%20tenets%20for%20this%20decision.%20Enough%20workers%20were%20dissatisfied%20enough%20to%20launch%20their%20own%20internal%20survey%20about%20RTO%2C%20an%20ironic%20Uno%20reverse%20card%20usage%20of%20the%20employee%20questionnaire%20to%20critique%20how%20little%20they%20felt%20the%20self-declared%20%26quot%3BEarth's%20Best%20Employer%26quot%3B%20was%20listening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20boss%20once%20lamented%20to%20me%20that%20surveys%20are%2C%20by%20design%2C%20akin%20to%20%26quot%3Binterviewing%20for%20pain%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20their%20intention%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20draw%20out%20complaints%20and%20gripes%20that%20aren't%20as%20serious%20as%20they%20seem.%20This%20may%20be%20true%2C%20but%20when%20you%20consider%20the%20total%20anonymity%20of%20the%20survey%2C%20how%20is%20a%20boss%20supposed%20to%20tell%20the%20genuine%20complaint%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-mainstream-google-traffic-stock-revenue-human-users-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EReddit-like%20bloviating%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20In%20a%20work%20world%20with%20increasingly%20labyrinthine%20and%20opaque%20hiring%20processes%2C%20the%20crisis%20of%20%26quot%3Bghost%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20built%20on%20the%20legacy%20of%20Michael%20Scott%20hating%20Toby%2C%20it's%20not%20surprising%20that%20we're%20mired%20in%20an%20ongoing%20HR%20credibility%20crisis%2C%20with%20so%20many%20workers%20rejecting%20the%20supposed%20efficacy%20and%20value%20of%20something%20as%20supposedly%20useful%20as%20surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20William%20Kahn%20about%20this%20hierarchical%20arrangement%20and%20fear%20of%20self-reporting%2C%20he%20tells%20me%20that%20%26quot%3Bideally%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20need%20for%20surveys%20that%20are%20in%20the%20service%20of%20helping%20managers%20understand%20the%20experiences%2C%20thoughts%2C%20and%20insights%20of%20their%20workers.%26quot%3B%20In%20an%20open%2C%20trusting%20workplace%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bcommunication%20would%20flow%20freely%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20work%20and%20healthy%20relationships%20matter%20more%20than%20the%20need%20of%20managers%20to%20be%20adored%20and%20obeyed.%26quot%3B%20Even%20so%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3Bsurveys%20would%20still%20be%20useful%20to%20get%20quick%20checks%20on%20the%20results%20of%20interventions%20designed%20to%20enable%20workers%20to%20fully%20engage%20their%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ended%20up%20not%20taking%20my%20CEO's%20stunning%20buyout%20offer.%20I%20was%20a%20diligent%2C%20productive%2C%20and%20engaged%20worker%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20the%20CEO%20was%20conflating%20and%20confusing%20this%20engagement%20with%20my%20happiness.%20Kahn%20tells%20me%20that%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20engaged%20members%20are%20satisfied%20with%20their%20roles%20and%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20they%20are%20'happy'%20or%20not%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20as%20much%20to%20do%20with%20the%20totality%20of%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20different%20matter.%26quot%3B%20More%20importantly%2C%20that%20CEO%20seemed%20to%20see%20the%20survey%20results%20as%20an%20end%20point%2C%20evidence%20of%20some%20unfixable%20condition%2C%20and%20not%20some%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-employee-engagement-workplace-morale-careers-boomers-gen-x-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkforce%20to%20maintain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nurture%2C%20and%20encourage.%20They%20supposed%20that%20if%20only%20we%20could%20have%20more%20engaged%20workers%2C%20we'd%20be%20better%20off%2C%20without%20contending%20that%20the%20survey%20revealed%20opportunity%2C%20not%20a%20definitive%20answer.%20It%20was%2C%20ironically%2C%20the%20moment%20I%20thought%20of%20most%20often%20when%20I%20did%20make%20the%20decision%20to%20leave%20the%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmatt-alston%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EMatt%20Alston%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E's%20writing%20has%20appeared%20in%20Wired%2C%20Rolling%20Stone%2C%20Playboy%2C%20and%20Believer.%20He%20trained%20as%20a%20civil%20engineer%2C%20and%20now%20works%20as%20a%20copywriter%20in%20tech.%20He%20lives%20in%20Maine%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20daughter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-sick-tired-engagement-surveys-managers-happiness-hr-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748333821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68308ca8c6ad288d1481c52a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-sick-tired-engagement-surveys-managers-happiness-hr-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20unhappy%20offices%2C%20managers%20are%20scrambling%20to%20survey%20the%20'quiet%20middle'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Matt%20Alston)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canon