Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20haven't%20seen%20it%20yet%2C%20go%20check%20out%20Airbnb%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaylor-swift-fans-eras-tour-ticketmaster-ftc-junk-fees-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETicketmaster%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FBooking.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBooking.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20StubHub%20and%20behold%20the%20magic%20that%20is%20all-in%20pricing.%20These%20platforms%2C%20which%20once%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20stacking%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-hidden-junk-fees-getting-worse-sneakier-prices-tickets-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehidden%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20consumers%20got%20to%20the%20checkout%20page%2C%20are%20now%20showing%20their%20costs%20up%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20because%20all%20these%20companies%20have%20had%20a%20collective%20epiphany%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20because%20the%20government%20is%20compelling%20them%20to%20be%20more%20transparent.%20On%20May%2012%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fbusiness-guidance%2Fresources%2Frule-unfair-or-deceptive-fees-frequently-asked-questions%23dynamicpricing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%2C%20bipartisan-supported%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20cracking%20down%20on%20unfair%20and%20deceptive%20fees%20went%20into%20effect.%20Per%20the%20FTC%2C%20the%20rule%20%26quot%3Bprohibits%20bait-and-switch%20pricing%20and%20other%20tactics%20used%20to%20obscure%20and%20misrepresent%20total%20prices%20and%20fees.%26quot%3B%20It%20only%20applies%20to%20live-event%20tickets%20and%20short-term%20lodging%2C%20meaning%20if%20you're%20renting%20a%20car%20or%20ordering%20delivery%2C%20you're%20still%20in%20fee%20hell.%20But%20for%20the%20sectors%20in%20question%2C%20it's%20the%20end%20of%20sneaky%20little%20charges%20that%20only%20show%20up%20at%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20your%20shopping%20journey.%20Yes%2C%20they%20can%20still%20charge%20you%20for%20whatever%20a%20%26quot%3Bconvenience%20fee%26quot%3B%20is%2C%20but%20they%20have%20to%20tell%20you%20that's%20what's%20happening%20from%20the%20get-go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20mundane%2C%20but%20this%20development%20is%20genuinely%20great.%20There's%20a%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.airbnb.com%2Ftotal-price-display-is-now-standard-globally%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbnb%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D169af597522ddf5f284bd3d9d378e572590e88658cdbd5004ce73ffec43c8b0b%26postID%3D682f2b8fb2c6efc60aa6f080%26postSlug%3Dall-in-pricing-airbnb-ticketmaster-ftc-hidden-fees-consumers-2025-5%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.ticketmaster.com%252Fwelcome%252Fall-in%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETicketmaster%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20trumpeted%20the%20moves%20(without%20drawing%20too%20much%20attention%20to%20why%20they're%20doing%20it).%20Disclosing%20costs%20up%20front%20improves%20competition%2C%20helps%20consumers%20make%20better%20decisions%2C%20and%20benefits%20businesses%20that%20have%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20transparency%20thing%20on%20their%20own.%20And%20people%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20this%20is%20something%20that%20makes%20common%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20we%20should%20be%20encouraging%20comparison%20shopping%2C%20especially%20when%20prices%20are%20high%20as%20it%20is%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20struggling%20to%20get%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Adam%20Rust%2C%20the%20director%20of%20financial%20services%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%2C%20a%20nonprofit.%20%26quot%3BIn%20any%20purchase%20choice%2C%20people%20examine%20the%20costs%20and%20the%20benefits%2C%20and%20if%20the%20costs%20are%20not%20clear%2C%20it's%20much%20harder%20to%20make%20a%20good%20choice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20felt%20that%20all-in%20pricing%20was%20a%20net%20positive%20for%20them%2C%20more%20would%20do%20it%20of%20their%20own%20volition.%20Instead%2C%20they%20use%20tactics%20such%20as%20drip%20pricing%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuhaul-truth-in-advertising-deceptive-bait-switch-pricing-allegation-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebait-and-switch%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20lure%20consumers%20in%20with%20a%20cheap%20up-front%20price%20before%20hitting%20them%20with%20a%20more%20expensive%20total.%20These%20tactics%20often%20get%20consumers%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20they%20bargained%20for%20%E2%80%94%20or%20spend%20anything%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20consumers%20are%20shopping%2C%20they%20pay%20the%20most%20attention%20to%20the%20rates%20that%20are%20shown%20most%20prominently%20to%20them%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20the%20first%20number%20they%20see.%20As%20they%20journey%20from%20the%20original%20ticket%20or%20hotel%20room%20price%20to%20the%20final%2C%20fee-loaded%20number%2C%20they're%20more%20invested%20in%20the%20purchase.%20Starting%20over%20again%20means%20eating%20some%20level%20of%20sunk%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20the%20consumer%20to%20reverse%2C%20because%20they%20understand%20you're%20already%20kind%20of%20committed%20to%20the%20transaction%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hal%20Singer%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Econ%20One%2C%20an%20economic%20consulting%20firm%2C%20and%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Utah.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20you%20literally%20show%20up%20at%20the%20resort%20when%20you%20learn%20about%20the%20fee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20make%20more%20money%20with%20the%20add-in%20fees%20at%20checkout.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubsonline.informs.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1287%2Fmksc.2020.1261%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20paper%20looked%20at%20the%20case%20of%20StubHub%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20showed%20up-front%20pricing%2C%20fees%20and%20all%2C%20from%20January%202014%20to%20August%202015.%20The%20pricing%20experiment%20was%20so%20short-lived%20in%20part%20because%20it%20cost%20StubHub%20money%3A%20The%20researchers%20found%20that%20disclosing%20fees%20from%20the%20get-go%20led%20to%20a%2028%25%20decline%20in%20overall%20revenue.%20Leaving%20the%20fees%20for%20the%20tail%20end%20of%20the%20transaction%20increased%20the%20quantity%20and%20quality%20of%20tickets%20bought%20%E2%80%94%20consumers%20bought%20more%20tickets%2C%20and%20they%20bought%20better%20(and%20more%20expensive)%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20companies%20do%20it%3F%20Because%20the%20revenues%20go%20up%20by%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Steven%20Tadelis%2C%20an%20economist%20professor%20at%20the%20Haas%20School%20of%20Business%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%20and%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20StubHub%20paper.%20%26quot%3BThis%20whole%20mechanism%20takes%20advantage%20of%20this%20bias%20that%20we%20have%2C%20where%20we're%20not%20taking%20these%20fees%20into%20account%2C%20and%20it%20ends%20up%20with%20us%20making%20purchases%20that%20we%20otherwise%20would%20not%20have%20made%20if%20we%20had%20all%20the%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStubHub%20executives%20had%20hoped%20consumers%20would%20reward%20them%20for%20their%20transparency%2C%20which%20isn't%20what%20happened%2C%20either.%20They%20were%20%26quot%3Bnever%20able%20to%20get%20that%20sweet%20love%20that%20they%20believed%20they%20would%20get%20after%20including%20all-in%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Tadelis%20says%2C%20because%20consumers%20didn't%20distinguish%20that%20StubHub's%20seemingly%20higher%20prices%20were%20because%20they%20included%20fees%20up%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20their%20competitors%20aren't%20forthcoming%20about%20prices%2C%20even%20well-meaning%20companies%20are%20hesitant%20to%20go%20out%20on%20a%20limb.%20They'll%20lose%20out%20on%20short-term%20revenue%20because%20consumers%20will%20just%20go%20for%20the%20cheaper-seeming%20option%2C%20and%20there's%20little%20evidence%20they'll%20get%20long-term%20goodwill%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20gives%20bad%20incentives%20to%20companies%20to%20try%20to%20tack%20things%20on%20at%20the%20last%20moment%2C%20because%20they%20know%20that%20then%20they%20could%20extract%20more%20rent%20from%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Michael%20Luca%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University's%20Carey%20Business%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFees%20also%20make%20things%20more%20complicated%2C%20which%20is%20the%20preferred%20corporate%20method%20for%20delivering%20less-than-ideal%20information.%20%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20when%20companies%20have%20bad%20news%2C%20they%20want%20to%20make%20it%20more%20complicated%20for%20customers%20to%20deal%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20have%20good%20news%2C%20they%20want%20to%20make%20it%20more%20transparent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20Sunday%20evening%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20ago%20looking%20at%20Airbnbs%20for%20a%20trip%20I%20didn't%20wind%20up%20taking.%20Besides%20the%20general%20excitement%20of%20picturing%20a%20fun%20mini%20vacation%2C%20the%20shopping%20experience%20itself%20was%20kind%20of%20awesome.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20set%20a%20%24500%20limit%20for%20what%20I%20wanted%20to%20spend%20on%20accommodations%20and%20browse%20accordingly.%20(This%20has%20been%20an%20optional%20search%20toggle%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20but%20now%20it's%20automatic.)%20I'm%20still%20a%20little%20sad%20that%20the%20trip%20didn't%20happen%20%E2%80%94%20I'd%20let%20myself%20get%20a%20little%20excited%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20getaway%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20would%20be%20much%20more%20annoyed%20if%20I%20had%20spent%20hours%20making%20spreadsheets%20comparing%20prices%20and%20mentally%20baking%20in%20a%20stack%20of%20fees%20only%20to%20wind%20up%20spending%20Memorial%20Day%20weekend%20on%20my%20couch%2C%20as%20was%20my%20destiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll-in%20pricing%20isn't%20something%20that%20many%20companies%20are%20likely%20to%20do%20on%20their%20own.%20The%20StubHub%20example%20proves%20there's%20little%20benefit%20to%20it%20if%20everyone%20else%20isn't%20going%20along.%20The%20ability%20to%20use%20drip%20and%20bait-and-switch%20pricing%20reduces%20competition%20and%20pushes%20up%20overall%20prices%2C%20because%20it%20stops%20people%20from%20being%20able%20to%20easily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-ecommerce-comparison-burnout-too-many-choices-overwhelming-decision-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomparison%20shop%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20seek%20out%20the%20best%20deals.%20In%20its%20war%20against%20what%20it%20dubbed%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-junk-fees-companies-biden-crackdown-lobbyists-fighting-rules-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejunk%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Biden%20administration%20estimated%20that%20consumers%20lost%20out%20on%20billions%20of%20dollars%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20and%20industries%20argue%20that%20consumers%20don't%20actually%20want%20all-in%20pricing.%20They%20say%20showing%20their%20full%20costs%20and%20fees%20up%20front%20would%20be%20too%20confusing%20to%20customers.%20Or%2C%20they%20say%20the%20add-on%20fees%20give%20them%20options%20to%20customize%20their%20purchases.%20This%20has%20an%20element%20of%20truth%20in%20some%20circumstances%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarry-on-bags-checked-luggage-size-charge-airlines-planes-travel-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaying%20extra%20to%20check%20a%20bag%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20pick%20a%20seat%20for%20a%20flight%20is%20a%20choice%20I'd%20like%20to%20have%20some%20control%20over.%20But%20I%20also%20don't%20think%20I'd%20be%20overwhelmed%20on%20Expedia%20or%20Google%20Flights%20if%20I%20did%20get%20a%20better%20sense%20early%20on%20of%20what%20options%20I%20might%20be%20signing%20up%20for%20when%20I%20buy%20a%20plane%20ticket%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20era%20of%20the%20dreaded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-basic-economy-review-carryon-middle-seat-new-york-denver-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebasic%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Also%2C%20in%20many%20industries%2C%20while%20fees%20are%20listed%20as%20extra%2C%20they're%20not%20optional.%20U-Haul%20tacks%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuhaul-truth-in-advertising-deceptive-bait-switch-pricing-allegation-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20fee%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20people%20can't%20get%20out%20of.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20delivery%20fees%20and%20service%20fees%20on%20food%20delivery%20apps%2C%20or%20the%20plethora%20of%20mysterious%20fees%20you%20see%20as%20you%20scrutinize%20receipts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20too%20hard%20for%20a%20company%20to%20know%20its%20price%20schedule%20and%20to%20put%20that%20on%20their%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20Rust%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20difficult%20as%20a%20shopper%20to%20go%20through%20the%20process%20of%20choosing%20a%20product%20and%20then%20putting%20it%20in%20the%20cart%20and%20then%20initiating%20payment%20and%20then%20finding%20out%20that%20the%20price%20is%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Wolfe%2C%20the%20counsel%20for%20Travelers%20United%2C%20a%20consumer%20travel%20advocacy%20nonprofit%2C%20points%20out%20that%20all-in%20pricing%20is%20popular%2C%20and%20again%2C%20that%20the%20new%20FTC%20rule%20had%20bipartisan%20support.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20truly%20one%20of%20the%20few%20issues%20in%20the%20country%20everyone%20agrees%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Legislation%20that%20would%20clamp%20down%20on%20resort%20fees%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2F