oach%20and%20chief%20program%20director%2C%20where%20he%20helps%20to%20design%20and%20administer%20AI%20hiring%20assessments%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKo%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20common%20for%20recruiters%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-interviews-ai-robots-how-to-prepare-keywords-advice-recruitment-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euse%20AI%20to%20screen%20job%20applicants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20includes%20video-based%20interviews%2C%20essay%20writing%2C%20job%20simulations%2C%20and%20psychometric%20tests%20to%20assess%20leadership%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKo%20said%20using%20AI%20allows%20recruiters%20to%20save%20time%20in%20the%20hiring%20process%20since%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20sift%20through%20hundreds%20or%20even%20thousands%20of%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20just%20five%20seconds%2C%20they%20will%20know%20if%20the%20candidate%20is%20compatible%20or%20competitive%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20tips%20Ko%20has%20for%20candidates%20looking%20to%20ace%20their%20AI%20hiring%20assessments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b91e1390-6a74-4fb7-aace-79c1e4e8291e%5C%22%3E1.%20The%20first%2030%20seconds%20matter%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Herman%20Ko%20presenting%20to%20students%20in%20a%20lecture%20theatre.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682ae62ec6ad288d148144fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKo%20worked%20at%20JPMorgan%20for%20about%203%20%C2%BD%20years%20before%20joining%20Career%20Hackers%20in%20March%202024.%3Cp%3EHerman%20Ko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKo%20said%20the%20first%2030%20seconds%20of%20a%20video%20interview%20matter.%20That's%20because%20it%20is%20roughly%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20a%20human%20recruiter%20will%20spend%20sampling%20random%20candidate%20clips%20during%20a%20hiring%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20observe%20is%20people%20only%20listen%20for%20the%20first%20few%20seconds%2C%20like%2010%20to%2020%20seconds%2C%20to%20make%20a%20judgment%20on%20how%20outspoken%20you%20are%2C%20your%20confidence%20level%2C%20your%20delivery%2C%20and%20then%20they%20rely%20on%20the%20AI%20generated%20transcript%20so%20they%20don't%20need%20to%20watch%20the%20entire%20video%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20having%20a%20very%20solid%20introduction%20can%20make%20a%20lasting%20impression%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221552d679-03de-44d2-a301-f0f67fd1f6be%5C%22%3E2.%20Think%20like%20a%20top%201%25%20candidate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKo%20said%20candidates%20need%20to%20give%20answers%20that%20can%20differentiate%20themselves%20as%20top-tier%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20statistics%2C%20only%20the%20top%201%25%20will%20make%20it%20into%20investment%20banks%20or%20top%20firms.%20That%20means%20you%20cannot%20say%20what%2099%25%20of%20the%20candidates%20will%20use%20in%20their%20responses%20because%20you%20will%20just%20be%20categorized%20as%20not%20competitive%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidates%20should%20instead%20take%20some%20time%20to%20think%20through%20their%20answers%20instead%20of%20launching%20into%20the%20first%20few%20points%20that%20come%20to%20mind%2C%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20think%20about%20what%20the%20average%20applicant%20will%20say.%20Usually%2C%20the%20first%20few%20things%20that%20pop%20into%20your%20head%20are%20those%20points%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20us%2C%20our%20AI%20tools%20compare%20the%20candidate's%20talking%20points%20and%20rate%20them%20accordingly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263f3567e-4918-4c1c-8cda-5a0df2a8e444%5C%22%3E3.%20Always%20maintain%20your%20professional%20image%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20AI%20assessments%20are%20often%20conducted%20in%20the%20comfort%20of%20one's%20home%2C%20Ko%20said%20candidates%20should%20strive%20to%20project%20a%20professional%20image%20through%20their%20attire%20and%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20firms%20will%20care%20about%20whether%20you%20are%20outspoken%20or%20professional%20enough%20to%20represent%20a%20firm.%20In%20terms%20of%20professional%20attire%2C%20of%20course%2C%20you%20should%20not%20wear%20a%20polo%20T-shirt%20in%20a%20video%20interview.%20You%20should%20always%20overdress%2C%20rather%20than%20underdress%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidates%20should%20also%20take%20their%20video%20interviews%20in%20a%20neat%20and%20tidy%20environment%2C%20Ko%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20do%20the%20video%20interviews%2C%20do%20not%20do%20it%20in%20a%20bedroom%20with%20clothes%20hanging%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20were%20recruiting%20for%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20law%20firms%20in%20the%20world%2C%20they%20got%20us%20to%20generate%20a%20candidate%20profile%20on%20what%20attire%20he%20or%20she%20wore%2C%20and%20how%20their%20background%20looked%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281c00eec-0dd3-4c78-b96c-b3bd02845f35%5C%22%3E4.%20Keep%20it%20natural%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKo%20said%20candidates%20should%20not%20try%20to%20read%20from%20a%20script%20in%20video%20interviews.%20This%20is%20because%20AI%20algorithms%20can%20pick%20up%20when%20candidates%20are%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20read%20from%20a%20script%2C%20your%20eyeballs%20will%20move%20in%20a%20zigzag%20pattern.%20It's%20easily%20noticeable%2C%20even%20for%20human%20sampling%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20candidates%2C%20Ko%20said%2C%20would%20try%20to%20include%20certain%20keywords%20in%20their%20responses%20to%20fool%20the%20AI%20into%20giving%20them%20a%20higher%20grade.%20Ko%20said%20such%20tricks%20would%20not%20work%20because%20there%20are%20usually%20anti-cheating%20mechanisms%20to%20track%20such%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKeep%20it%20natural.%20Try%20not%20to%20go%20too%20fast%20and%20ensure%20you%20have%20a%20clear%20pronunciation.%20Sometimes%2C%20when%20candidates%20are%20nervous%2C%20they%20will%20just%20give%20rapid-fire%20responses.%20But%20the%20thing%20is%2C%20if%20they%20do%20it%20too%20fast%20or%20not%20too%20clearly%2C%20the%20AI%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20capture%20your%20speech%20and%20build%20an%20accurate%20transcript%20to%20analyze%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20human%20assessor%20cannot%20judge%20your%20points%20based%20on%20the%20transcript.%20So%2C%20make%20sure%20to%20go%20a%20little%20bit%20slower%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20AI%20can%20capture%20what%20you%20are%20talking%20about%20clearly%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228727f527-8e8d-47d2-b1c9-a7f62984d1e4%5C%22%3E5.%20Do%20not%20use%20AI%20in%20interviews%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20candidates%20are%20being%20assessed%20by%20AI%20doesn't%20mean%20they%20should%20use%20AI%20tools%20to%20prepare%20for%20interviews%2C%20Ko%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20most%20assessment%20platforms%20have%20built-in%20detection%20mechanisms%20to%20identify%20AI-generated%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20use%20AI%2C%20there%20is%20a%20unique%20language%20pattern%20for%20those%20AI-generated%20responses%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20their%20arguments%20and%20their%20examples%20are%20all%20the%20same.%20Even%20the%20sequence%20and%20wording%20are%20exactly%20the%20same%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20namedropping%20examples%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20there's%20deepfake%20technology%2C%20where%20candidates%20can%20get%20someone%20more%20%26quot%3Btalented%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Boutspoken%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20the%20interview%20on%20their%20behalf%2C%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20tools%20these%20days%20are%20now%20very%20advanced%20as%20well.%20We%20can%20also%20catch%20candidates%20using%20deepfakes%2C%20and%20we%20also%20have%20facial%20recognition%3Cbr%3Etools%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20candidates%20looking%20to%20land%20a%20job%20need%20to%20understand%20how%20critical%20these%20AI%20hiring%20assessments%20are%2C%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20candidates%20are%20like%2C%20'I%20will%20just%20prepare%20for%20the%20Superday.%20I%20will%20just%20prepare%20for%20the%20group%20interviews.'%20But%20if%20they%20don't%20manage%20to%20pass%20this%20round%2C%20there's%20nothing%20out%20there%20for%20them.%20So%20it%20is%20really%20worth%20the%20energy%20to%20do%20some%20drills%20on%20these%20kinds%20of%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20Ko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-shares-5-tips-acing-ai-interviews-tests-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748304481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6826f5c168a2929008017fe1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-shares-5-tips-acing-ai-interviews-tests-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20increasingly%20turning%20to%20AI%20tools%20to%20conduct%20screening%20interviews%2C%20says%20career%20coach%20Herman%20Ko.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A96%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-shares-5-tips-acing-ai-interviews-tests-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Benson%20Boone%20on%20Life%20After%20Opening%20for%20Taylor%20Swift%20and%20Why%20Bruno%20Mars%20is%20His%20Dream%20Collaborator%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%2